## Architectural Invariants (v1.0.0-rc5)

1. Fixed 4th-order DPW kernel
2. `i128` (Q124) differentiation buffers
3. `Scalar` (`I64F64`) phase engine with O(1) modulo normalization
4. Pure fixed-point arithmetic
5. `S32LE` normative egress
6. Advisory `f64` shadow model (non-normative; excluded from hashing)

---

## Canonical Signal Flow

```text
[ Phase Engine (Scalar 128) ]
             |
             v
      [ Truncation (Q31 → Q30) ]
             |
             v
      [ x² Polynomial (Q124) ]
             |
             v
      [ x⁴ Polynomial (Q124) ]
             |
             v
 [ 3rd-Order Differentiation (i128) ]
             |
             v
  [ Gain (1/24) ]
             |
             v
  [ Egress Headroom (>> HEADROOM_BITS) ]
             |
             v
      [ Saturation → i32 (S32LE) ]
```

The `S32LE` egress is the normative observation boundary.
Internal state remains 128-bit and `i128`.

Higher-precision taps must not alter evolution or participate in reference hashing.

